<Content>Rude, Nasty Staff, Dirty Room, Horrible ! We saw an ad for this hotel in Que Pasa magazine and thought it mught be nice. But be warned, there is NO BEACH, what they call a beach is a small strip in front of someone else's home. When we got there, the staff in the front desk is rude and nasty. They placed us on the 3rd floor and there are NO ELEVATORS and we have very heavy luggage. We asked for a room in the 1st floor but again we were rudely informed that the hotel was fully booked. Our car was the only car in the parking lot and I realized that evening that we were the only people in that hotel because their restaurant is also empty. We got out of there early the following day, and we asked if they have continental breakfast, coffee and some toast and again we were informed rudely that we have to pay for it. So we got out of there by 7 AM the following day. NEVER AGAIN ! 
