<Content>So-so Ok, my biggest complaint was the attitude of the staff. The room was clean, tho of all the places we stayed it was the only one with carpets. I like the tile floors that everyone else had - the are cleaner. Otherwise, for the money it was a good value. Didn't go to the pool or the beach it was a one nite stay - Christmas nite. Dinnerin the restaurant was decent, but not great. The early wait staff had no idea about many items on the menu. The second shift came on while we were there and I will say he seemed more competent. Breakfast was another story, quite good and plenty of food served by the pool with a smile from a nice young lady. The front desk personal were cold and not very accommodating, but they did locate face cloths when we asked. 
