<Author>A TripAdvisor Member
<Content>Be warned Stayed here 2 days with my sister; we both know island very well. We stayed at Perichi's on business, not vacation. The brochure for Perichi's, as well as a lot of the PR tourist literature, is misleading. There is no beach in walking distance, at least not any you'd like to bathe in. There is a picture of a beautiful beach in the brochure but if it is the beach the receptionist claimed it was, it is a long car-ride away, and I suspect that it was taken a long time ago when it was still nice. The waterfront by Perichi's is completely covered by a string of eateries and houses, not all in the best condition. The pool faces the parkinglot. The most basic rooms, in the main building, are musty smelling, have no hangers in closet.On plus side, it was clean, staff is very nice and restaurant is good. Eateries along water have good local food. 
