<Author>ILfemale
<Content>Pleasant Stay We stayed at this hotel during our recent week-long stay in Puerto Rico, and it was a welcome relief after our hotel in San Juan (reviewed elsewhere.)The hotel was surprisingly empty for January, prime time for a getaway to a warm place by most Midwesterners. I saw no fellow tourists at the hotel the first night, and just a couple on the second night.The Sea is across the street, but behind a row of builidings, with only a small viewing area to walk out by the water.The pool area is nice to sit out on, even if you don't swim. Breakfast is served on a covered verenda overlooking the pool area in the a.m., including fresh pineapple or other locally-grown produce. Out of four hotels we stayed in in Puerto Rico, this was the only one that had carpets on the floors. Hard ceramic tiles seem to the norm elsewhere. The air conditioning was very functional -- especially when the cleaning people turned it down to 17 celcius in our absence! Curtains on the patio doors are quite thin, and the clatter of a nearby school can be heard quite early in the morning, but otherwise this is a nice quiet and private getaway. 
